<%# Shared sidebar/topbar/footer chrome for both consoles (Admin, SuperAdmin) — ported from the
    webadmin template's pages-starter.html vertical-layout variant (requirement.md §5.14; see
    vendor/webadmin_template/pages-starter.html for the source). Only the vertical sidebar layout
    is used; the template's alternate horizontal-topbar markup and its theme-customizer right
    sidebar (RTL/dark-mode/layout-switcher demo controls) are intentionally not ported — this is a
    product, not a template showcase. Sidebar collapse + MetisMenu init are Stimulus-controlled
    (app/javascript/controllers/sidebar_controller.js) instead of loading the template's app.js
    wholesale, which assumes demo-only DOM we don't ship.

    Rendered via `render layout: "shared/console_shell", locals: { ... } do ... end` from
    layouts/admin.html.erb and layouts/super_admin.html.erb — the block becomes `yield` below,
    i.e. the actual page content. Locals:
      home_path            — user_root_path / platform_staff_root_path — no bare root_path exists,
                              every route carries its console's /admin or /platform namespace
                              (config/routes.rb)
      nav_items           — Array of { path:, icon:, label: } — see app/helpers/{admin,super_admin}_helper.rb
      footer_text          — String, e.g. "xEvent" / "xEvent Platform"
      user_dropdown        — Hash of locals for shared/_user_dropdown, or nil if signed out
      back_link            — optional Hash { label:, path:, context:, context_subtitle: } —
                              currently only layouts/admin.html.erb, whenever the event-scoped
                              sidebar is showing (AdminHelper#event_nav_items, requirement.md
                              §5.14 v12). Mirrors shopmate-backend's own tenant-context sidebar
                              (app/views/layouts/_sidebar.html.erb in that repo) exactly, both
                              pieces of it: an identity card (`context:`/`context_subtitle:` —
                              here, the selected event's name/status) directly above the nav <ul>,
                              then `label:`/`path:` rendered as the first item *inside* that <ul>
                              (a real menu <li>, bx-arrow-back icon, not a separate muted-text
                              element bolted on above the menu) — so the card answers "what am I
                              looking at" and the very next thing below it is "leave." `context:`
                              is optional independently of `label:`/`path:` — nil skips just the
                              card, keeping the back link on its own if a future caller ever wants
                              that. Omit `back_link` itself entirely elsewhere; no default "back to
                              X" makes sense for the account-level sidebar.
      impersonator         — Phase 23 (doc/implementation_3.md): optional User, the real Super
                              Admin behind an impersonated tenant session
                              (Admin::BaseController#current_impersonator) — only ever passed by
                              layouts/admin.html.erb; omitted entirely elsewhere, same convention
                              back_link already takes, since impersonation only ever happens on the
                              tenant Admin Console.

    Topbar shows a static welcome message (ported from shopmate-backend's _upper_header.html.erb,
    same template family) rather than the per-page title — that now lives in the content area
    itself, via shared/_page_header's breadcrumb + <h4> (content_for(:page_title) still drives the
    browser <title> tag, shared/_head.html.erb). %>
<%# data-controller="confirm-dialog" lives here, not per-trigger, so any button anywhere in the
    page content can use a plain data-action="click->confirm-dialog#show" (see
    shared/_confirm_dialog.html.erb) without redeclaring it — Stimulus resolves an action to the
    nearest ancestor carrying the matching data-controller, same as data-action="sidebar#toggle"
    below already relies on this element for the sidebar controller. download-progress (shared/
    _download_progress_modal.html.erb) lives here for the same reason. %>
<% if local_assigns[:impersonator] %>
  <%# Phase 23 (doc/implementation_3.md): rendered as a SIBLING of #layout-wrapper, not a child —
      application.css's own transform trick makes #layout-wrapper the containing block for its
      OWN `position: fixed` descendants; a banner nested inside it would itself get shifted down
      by the same margin-top meant to push the topbar/sidebar out from under it (caught live: the
      banner ended up at the topbar's new position instead of the true viewport top). %>
  <%= render "shared/impersonation_banner", impersonator: impersonator, impersonated: current_user %>
<% end %>
<div id="layout-wrapper" data-controller="sidebar confirm-dialog download-progress">
  <%# class="isvertical-topbar" — load-bearing, not decorative: app.min.css positions
      #page-topbar via `.isvertical-topbar{position:fixed;left:270px;...}` (offset past the
      fixed-position sidebar's own width). Without it the topbar renders at its static in-flow
      position instead, landing underneath/behind the sidebar — invisible, not just misplaced.
      Confirmed against both the original template mockup (vendor/webadmin_template/
      pages-starter.html) and shopmate-backend's own _header.html.erb, which both carry this
      class; missing here since Phase 0, undetected until real topbar content (the page-title
      text, now shared/_page_header's breadcrumb) made the occlusion visible. %>
  <header id="page-topbar" class="isvertical-topbar">
    <div class="navbar-header">
      <div class="d-flex">
        <div class="navbar-brand-box">
          <%= render "shared/brand_link", home_path: home_path %>
        </div>

        <button type="button" class="btn btn-m px-3 font-size-24 header-item waves-effect" data-action="sidebar#toggle">
          <i class="bx bx-menu align-middle"></i>
        </button>

        <div class="page-title-box align-self-center d-none d-md-block">
          <h4 class="page-title mb-0">Welcome back!</h4>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="d-flex">
        <%= render "shared/user_dropdown", **user_dropdown if user_dropdown %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="vertical-menu">
    <div class="navbar-brand-box">
      <%= render "shared/brand_link", home_path: home_path %>
    </div>

    <div class="sidebar-menu-scroll">
      <%# Identity card for whatever back_link[:context] names (here, the selected event) — same
          avatar-circle-initial + bold-name(+muted-subtitle) shape as shopmate-backend's own
          tenant identity card, directly above the nav <ul> whose first item is the back link
          below (see that local's own doc comment above). Background color (rgba(31,88,199,0.06)
          — a faint tint of the template's own primary blue) copied verbatim from that same
          shopmate-backend partial, not approximated from this app's own Bootstrap palette. %>
      <% if local_assigns[:back_link] && back_link[:context] %>
        <div class="px-3 py-3 border-bottom" style="background: rgba(31,88,199,0.06);">
          <div class="d-flex align-items-center gap-2">
            <div class="avatar-xs flex-shrink-0">
              <span class="avatar-title rounded-circle bg-primary text-white font-size-14 fw-bold">
                <%= back_link[:context].first.upcase %>
              </span>
            </div>
            <div class="overflow-hidden">
              <p class="mb-0 fw-semibold text-truncate" style="font-size: 13px;"><%= back_link[:context] %></p>
              <% if back_link[:context_subtitle] %>
                <p class="mb-0 text-muted" style="font-size: 11px;"><%= back_link[:context_subtitle] %></p>
              <% end %>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      <% end %>

      <div id="sidebar-menu">
        <ul class="metismenu list-unstyled" id="side-menu" data-sidebar-target="menu">
          <%# "Back to X" — same markup/placement as shopmate-backend's own back-to-tenant-list
              link (app/views/layouts/_sidebar.html.erb in that repo, same template family):
              first item in the list, ahead of the "Menu" title, a real <li> using the list's own
              icon/label markup (bx-arrow-back, not a differently-styled element bolted on above
              the menu) so it reads as part of the same list, not a separate widget. %>
          <% if local_assigns[:back_link] %>
            <li>
              <%= link_to back_link[:path], class: "waves-effect" do %>
                <i class="bx bx-arrow-back icon nav-icon"></i> <span class="menu-item"><%= back_link[:label] %></span>
              <% end %>
            </li>
          <% end %>
          <li class="menu-title">Menu</li>
          <% nav_items.each do |item| %>
            <li>
              <%= link_to item[:path], class: "waves-effect" do %>
                <i class="bx <%= item[:icon] %> icon nav-icon"></i> <span class="menu-item"><%= item[:label] %></span>
              <% end %>
            </li>
          <% end %>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="main-content">
    <div class="page-content">
      <div class="container-fluid">
        <%= yield %>
      </div>
    </div>

    <footer class="footer">
      <div class="container-fluid">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-6">&copy; <%= Date.current.year %> <%= footer_text %>.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </div>

  <%# Inside #layout-wrapper (unlike shared/confirm_dialog just below, a plain document
      .getElementById lookup that doesn't care where it lives) — download_progress_controller.js
      uses real Stimulus targets, which only resolve within the declaring element's own subtree. %>
  <%= render "shared/download_progress_modal" %>
</div>

<%= render "shared/flash" %>
<%= render "shared/confirm_dialog" %>
